ebusctl
-----------

Usage:
 ebusctl [Options] Command [Arguments]

Description:
 'ebusctl' is a tcp/udp socket client for ebusgate.
  hint: try 'help' for available ebusgate commands.

Options:

-s | --server	name or ip (localhost)
-p | --port	port (8888)
-u | --udp	connect via udp

   | --values
   | --version
-h | --help



$ ebusctl help

commands:
 open         - open ebus connection
 close        - close ebus connection

 send         - write message onto ebus 'send ZZPBSBNNDx'

 subscribe    - start forwarding ebus messages 'subscribe [-s server] [-p port] [filter]'
 unsubscribe  - stop forwarding ebus messages 'unsubscribe [-s server] [-p port] [filter]'

 active       - enable/disable active ebus mode

 dump         - enable/disable raw data dumping

 loglevel     - change logging level 'loglevel level'
 lograw       - enable/disable raw data logging

 stop         - stop running daemon and exit
 quit         - close tcp connection

 help         - print this page



ebusfeed
------------

Usage:
 ebusfeed [Options] /path/dumpfile

Description:
 'ebusfeed' sends hex values from dump file to a pseudo terminal device (pty)

  Example: 1. 'socat -d -d pty,raw,echo=0 pty,raw,echo=0'
           2. create symbol links to appropriate devices
              for example: 'ln -s /dev/pts/5 /dev/ttyUSB5'
                           'ln -s /dev/pts/6 /dev/ttyUSB6'
           3. start ebusgate: 'ebusgate -f -n -d /dev/ttyUSB5'
           4. start ebusfeed: 'ebusfeed -d /dev/ttyUSB6 /path/to/ebus_dump.bin'

Options:

-d | --device	link on pseudo terminal device (/dev/ttyUSB)
-t | --time	delay between 2 bytes in 'us' (10000)

   | --values
   | --version
-h | --help



For bugs and missing features use github issue system.

The author can be contacted at roland.jax@liwest.at.
